DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
"parserFormulaUpToConstant.pl",
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Vector");

$a = random(2,10,1);

$ansb = Compute("0.1618*e^2*0.739*x")->with(tolerance => .1, tolType => 'absolute');

$ansc = Compute("1/2*e^2*x+0.5");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT

I am interested in finding an anti-derivative for \(f(x)=e^{2x}\).
$BR
$BR
a. Using Excel and 100 subintervals of \(0 \leq x \leq 2\), compute an approximate area function for \(f(x)\). Find a best fitting curve that fits the data well. (It may help to use a secondary axis for the area data.)
$BR
\(F(x) \approx\) \{ans_rule()\}
$BR
$BR
b. Based on your best fitting curve, use guess and check to find the anti-derivative.
$BR
\(F(x)=\) \{ans_rule()\}


END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

ANS( $ansb->cmp()); 
ANS( $ansc->cmp()); 

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_SOLUTION
${PAR}SOLUTION:${PAR}

a. \(F(x) \approx $ansb\)
$BR
$BR
b. \(F(x)=$ansc\)

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

COMMENT('MathObject version.');

ENDDOCUMENT();
